panels.description:
The OverOps dashboard (app.overops.com) provides  **Dev + QA** a detailed analysis of errors within the target applications and direct links to Root cause.
\
\
[![OverOps](https://github.com/takipi/overops-influx-backend/blob/master/grafana/public/img/classic-preview.png?raw=true)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=5&v=QbQxKYl2RgA)
panels.title: OverOps Classic

panels.description:
The Reliability Analysis  dashboard provides **Dev** with a list of all new, increasing errors and slowdowns within the environment and direct links to their root cause.
\
\
[![Root Cause](https://github.com/takipi/overops-influx-backend/blob/master/grafana/public/img/reliability-analysis-preview.png?raw=true)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GoV08HPfnaQ&list=PLmktsLXcysU-J1jEfD6XnNKmcL7mAppu1&index=12)
panels.title: Root Cause (Dev)

panels.description:
The Reliability Scorecard dashboard enables **QA + Dev** to verify the code quality and reliability of applications and deployments.
\
\
[![Scorecard](https://github.com/takipi/overops-influx-backend/blob/master/grafana/public/img/scorecard-preview.png?raw=true)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=auzmOqVwUPQ&list=PLmktsLXcysU-J1jEfD6XnNKmcL7mAppu1&index=9)
panels.title: Scorecard (QA)

panels.description:
The Site Reliability enables **DevOps + SRE** to observe the reliability of transactions and applications within the environment in real-time.
\
\
[![SRE](https://github.com/takipi/overops-influx-backend/blob/master/grafana/public/img/site-reliability-preview.png?raw=true)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5e-A8alv40o&list=PLmktsLXcysU-J1jEfD6XnNKmcL7mAppu1&index=8)
panels.title: Site Reliability (SRE)

panels.description:
The Errors dashboard enables **Dev + QA** to analyze and prioritize errors within the environment, ranked by severity.
\
\
\
[![Errors](https://github.com/takipi/overops-influx-backend/blob/master/grafana/public/img/errors-preview.png?raw=true)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3zTABDJjrqU&list=PLmktsLXcysU-J1jEfD6XnNKmcL7mAppu1&index=13)
panels.title: Errors

panels.description:
The Transactions dashboard enables **SREs and DevOps** to observe the performance and reliability of transactions within their environment.
\
\
[![Transactions](https://github.com/takipi/overops-influx-backend/blob/master/grafana/public/img/transactions-preview.png?raw=true)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n-gRIl-8BSE&list=PLmktsLXcysU-J1jEfD6XnNKmcL7mAppu1&index=11)
panels.title: Transactions

panels.description:
The Event Diff dashboard enables **QA and Dev** to compare any set of applications and deployments to see which errors have been introduced or increased **release over release** or between different time periods (e.g. today vs. last week).
\
\
[![Diff](https://github.com/takipi/overops-influx-backend/blob/master/grafana/public/img/diff-preview.png?raw=true)](https://youtu.be/iUjmc9vMy_Q)
panels.title: Event Diff

panels.description:
The Reliability Review dashboard enables **execs + managers** to review how application quality trends across different reliability KPIs such as score, new errors and volume over time, and compare different applications.
\
\
[![Trend](https://github.com/takipi/overops-influx-backend/blob/master/grafana/public/img/reliability-review-trend.png?raw=true)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SacZ8cWuxGI&list=PLmktsLXcysU-J1jEfD6XnNKmcL7mAppu1&index=2&t=0s)
panels.title: Trend

panels.description: A report providing a weighted score of the key applications, as defined in the Settings dashboard. Key applications are marked with * and appear at the top of the list followed by applications with the highest event volume up to limit of  $limit applications in total. Score weights are defined in the Settings dashboard.

<script>

function hide(name) {
  var element = document.getElementsByClassName(name);
  
  if ((element) && (element.length == 1)) {
    element[0].style.display = 'none';
  }

}

function hideButtons() {
  hide("btn navbar-button gf-timepicker-nav-btn");
  hide("navbar-buttons navbar-buttons--zoom");
  hide("btn navbar-button navbar-button--zoom");
}

hideButtons();

</script>
